modules.description: This module provides functions to convert bit vectors to and from strings, with the least significant bit first, and to print them using a formatter. It operates on the abstract `Bitv.t` type, representing bit vectors as sequences of boolean values. Use cases include serializing bit vectors for storage or transmission and debugging via formatted output.

This module provides functions to convert bit vectors to and from string representations, using a most-significant-bit-first ordering. It supports rendering bit vectors as strings, parsing them from strings, and printing them using OCaml's formatted output. These operations are useful when serializing bit vectors for storage or transmitting them in a human-readable format.
